I’ve had plenty of fried griot and it always comes with fried plantains.. I hope the owner takes into consideration what I’m saying. The meat should be fried and fried well. The skin of the griot should be crispy (no not burnt either) but in their case it was just mushy. The plantains were fresh and done beautifully in size. Now the Piklis is missing that spice. As for price why are people being charged different prices for the same thing. Please be consistent with the pricing and the food. I never want to give a poor review to a place but I am a foodie and do reviews of restaurants on Instagram/ blogs and Facebook.  Please do better because I know you guys can. You are a small business so please be consistent with everything  Sincerely,

The price of the food changes according to who the cashier is. There is light complected female cashier who I suspect is making up her own prices or there is a gross lack of communication amongst the workers.  A couple  of weeks ago I ordered a small griot and was charged 6.50.  Keep in mind not too long ago, the price was raised to 6 dollars from 5.50. I did not say anything and took my food and went about my way.   Approximately 2 weeks later, I go to store and another cashier is working  states the price of a small griot is 6.00 dollars.  Both times were in the afternoon. Today, I go to the store at around 11am this and the same light complected female is working the cashier register and  was charged 6.50 for a small griot. Three days ago, it was 6.00.  I could mistaken but the light complected cashier does not give receipts. On Postmates, the griot is also 6 dollars.

I moved to Canarsie one year ago, bebe fritay is where I always go to whenever I want a take-out food, yes the wait is always long but the employees have always been polite and calm while serving you the ones I knew have always been respectful. However there's a new employee today that I have seen for the first time omg she is rude, very disrespectful, I waited almost an hour just for her to serve one customer. I am truly concerned not because she is Haitian working in a Haitian business that she should behave like a low-class person. no offense she is so rude and disrespectful. I was mad for waiting for almost an hour instead of her ignore or apologize for the wait she started cursing and using bad words as if I should be the one apologizing and flattered her. she got to understand that in every business CUSTOMERS should be put first. I am a sale associate and if I was speaking to a customer this bad I would have got fired. PLEASE MAKE A DIFFERENCE  her place is not there. don't get me wrong the food is amazing the other's employees I knew for a year are cool and kind but this new one is a no go I swear.
